This problems arises from the fact that the derived Association#endType 
feature may contain null values, violating a basic assumption in EMF that no 
feature, derived or not, should contain null values. Nonetheless, the EMF team 
has agreed to allow for this possibility in their cross reference utility in 
EMF 2.1.

In the meantime, the problem can be worked around using a custom cross 
referencer as follows (for example):

new EcoreUtil.ExternalCrossReferencer(resource) {
  protected boolean crossReference(EObject eObject, EReference eReference, 
EObject crossReferencedEObject) {
    return null == crossReferencedEObject ? false : super.crossReference
(eObject, eReference, crossReferencedEObject);
  }
  public Map findExternalCrossReferences() {
    return super.findExternalCrossReferences();
  }
}.findExternalCrossReferences();
